          "prompt_html": "<h1>MULTIPLE CHOICE 20</h1><p><strong>Questions 31 - 35</strong></p><p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A, B or C</strong>.</p><p>31 Why do most people come to Vostok Station by boat and then on foot?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Flights are too expensive.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Snow conditions stop planes most of the year.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    It’s less dangerous.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>32 What is <strong>NOT</strong> an initial problem that polar scientists at Vostok Station experience after arrival?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    They experience headaches.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    They keep falling asleep.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    They are sick.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>33 Why were the Russian scientists initially drilling at Vostok Station?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    For oil</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Ice cores</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    For minerals</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>34 What stopped the Russian scientists drilling?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    The ice was so clean.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Fresh water appeared at the drill head.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Heat was apparent around the drill tip.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>35 What new life has already been found by scientists in Lake Vostok?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    The protist organism</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Organisms from the time of the creation of the earth</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Previously unidentified microorganisms</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table>",
